  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is aimed at increasing the safety of the use of anaesthesia in an elderly
      population (&gt; 60 years). Patients with decreased physiological reserve, including all elderly
      patients, have an increased risk of getting an erroneous induction bolus. This project will
      investigate how fast elderly patients (&gt; 60 years) fall asleep during bolus induction of
      anaesthesia with two of the most used hypnotics, thiopental and propofol, evaluated with
      BIS-monitoring and clinical signs of anaesthetic depth. The hemodynamic response will also be
      evaluated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
